(define/contract (check-strings s1 s2)
  (-> string? string? boolean?)
  ; Create two vectors (for even and odd indices) of size 26 to count the frequency of each letter
  ; 'a' to 'z' in both strings, since we are dealing with lowercase English letters only.
  (let ([even-counts1 (make-vector 26 0)]
        [odd-counts1 (make-vector 26 0)]
        [even-counts2 (make-vector 26 0)]
        [odd-counts2 (make-vector 26 0)])
    ; Iterate over the strings to fill the frequency vectors.
    (for ([i (in-range (string-length s1))])
      (let ([index (- (char->integer (string-ref s1 i)) (char->integer #\a))]
            [parity (modulo i 2)])
        (vector-set! (if (= parity 0) even-counts1 odd-counts1) index
                     (+ 1 (vector-ref (if (= parity 0) even-counts1 odd-counts1) index))))
      (let ([index (- (char->integer (string-ref s2 i)) (char->integer #\a))]
            [parity (modulo i 2)])
        (vector-set! (if (= parity 0) even-counts2 odd-counts2) index
                     (+ 1 (vector-ref (if (= parity 0) even-counts2 odd-counts2) index)))))
    ; Compare the frequency vectors for both even and odd indices.
    (and (equal? even-counts1 even-counts2) (equal? odd-counts1 odd-counts2))))
